Brenda Moore, IA, daughter of
Mr.. and Mrs. Wardell Moore,
lib West Grant, was selected
to represent Phoenix Union High
School freshman girls on Sears
Teen Fashion Board.


She is pictured modelling a
back to school fashion at re-
cent program.


Brenda graduated from the
eighth grade of Booker T. Wash
ington School this June. She plans
to become a medical technician
after completing high school.


She is interested in music and
plays piano for the youth choir
at The Church of the Living God
PCT. She enjoys her dancing and
piano lessons.


Active in the activities of Girl
Scouts Troop S, Brenda served
as youth counselor, also. Her
favorite composer is Bach and
her favorite musician in the
modern manner is Ramsey
Lewis. Debbie Reynolds is her
favorite movie star.

Welcome back to all vaca-
toners.


Mrs. Roscoe H. Adams of St.
Louis, Mo-, is the houseguest of
Moss Gwen Reed.


Sandra and Sherry Vance Of Po-
mona, Calf, are visiting their
grandparents, Mr.. and Mrs. VIII
Galloway.


Sgt. and Mrs. Arthur Robertson
and children have visited his
parents, Mr.. and Mrs. Preston
Robertson of Duquesne, Pa, and
their uncle and aunt, Mr.. and Mrs.
C. Collier of Imperial, Kansas.


Rev. and Mrs. Rufus McClain
of Odessa, Texas, are visiting
Rev. and Mrs. L. ]. Dunbar.
He was one of the guest speakers
at the Dunbars' anniversary pro-
gram.


Rev. and Mrs. Allison Reid
have returned from their vaca-
ton in California.


For the first time in Phoenix,
a singing convention by the Gospel
Velvet Tones will be held at
Emmanuel Church Of God in
Christ, 18th and E. Madison,
Aug. "a = 80.


Arizona State Baptist BTU and
Sunday School Congress IS
holding sessions at St. John
Baptist Church. The public is
invited to attend the annual presi-
dents address Friday, Aug. FL,
1870 pm.


Rev. C. N. HALLS the president
and Rev. F. ]. Winbush Of Tucson
is the general president.


The most enjoyment Of the
weekend was at the Debonairs
South Mountain Park partyS atur-
day night. Everyone enjoyed
delicious barbecued steaks and
chickens.


The youth of Union Baptist
Church, 2845 E. Chapman are
raising funds at a car wash
Saturday at the church. Stop
and help them.


Thought of the week Too
much disputing puts the truth
to flight. Italian proverb.
